---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const seo = {"title": "Threads — Smooth Threads | D‑Essence Wellness", "description": "Collagen‑stimulating threads for subtle refinement and firmness.", "canonical": "/services/smooth-threads", "type": "website", "ogImage": "/og-default" };
---

<BaseLayout {...seo}>

<section class="relative isolate bg-[#FAFAF8] text-[#161615]">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pt-28 md:pt-32 pb-24">
    <!-- Masthead / breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mb-3 tracking-wide">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-800">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-1">/</span>
      <a href="/services" class="hover:text-neutral-800">Services</a>
      <span class="mx-1">/</span>
      <span class="text-neutral-800">Threads — Smooth Threads</span>
    </nav>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-[2.5rem] md:text-6xl leading-[1.05] font-semibold tracking-tight">Threads — Smooth Threads</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-neutral-700 max-w-2xl">Collagen‑stimulating threads for subtle refinement and firmness.</p>
      <div class="mt-4 h-px w-full bg-neutral-200"></div>
    </header>

    <!-- Body: two-column flow on desktop -->
    <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-h2:mt-0 prose-h2:mb-2 prose-h3:mt-6 prose-h3:mb-2">
      <style is:global>
        @media (min-width: 1024px) {
          .editorial-columns {
            column-count: 2;
            column-gap: 3rem;
          }
        }
        .dropcap:first-letter {
          float: left;
          font-size: 3.25rem;
          line-height: 1;
          padding-right: .25rem;
          padding-top: .15rem;
          font-weight: 600;
        }
        .pullquote {
          border-left: 2px solid #0a0a0a;
          padding-left: .85rem;
          font-style: italic;
          color: #404040;
          margin: 1.25rem 0;
        }
      </style>

      <!-- 1) Description -->
      <h2 id="description">Description</h2>
      <div class="editorial-columns">
        <p class="dropcap">
          This service aims for refined, natural‑looking improvement while preserving character and expression.
          We begin with a brief consultation to map goals, review medical history, and outline a plan that fits your timeline.
        </p>
        <p>
          Technique, dosing, or device settings are chosen to suit the indication and area. We explain what the service can and cannot accomplish,
          and where adjuncts or alternatives may serve you better.
        </p>
        <p class="pullquote">“Clarity, restraint, and precision—so results look like you, on a rested day.”</p>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-10 border-neutral-200">

      <!-- 2) Benefits -->
      <h2 id="benefits">Benefits</h2>
      <div class="editorial-columns">
        <p>
          Most guests appreciate a plan that favors harmony over extremes. Benefits commonly include a more polished appearance,
          guidance for a smooth recovery, and realistic expectations that remove guesswork.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Plan tailored to your anatomy and goals</li>
          <li>Comfort‑forward techniques and pacing</li>
          <li>Clear, concise aftercare</li>
          <li>Quality products/devices and trained providers</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-10 border-neutral-200">

      <!-- 3) How It Works -->
      <h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>
      <div class="editorial-columns">
        <p>
          We match the modality to the mapped indication. That can mean refined dosing, device parameters, or layered approaches when appropriate.
          We also account for your tolerance, schedule, and desired subtlety so the cadence feels sustainable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-10 border-neutral-200">

      <!-- 4) The Process -->
      <h2 id="the-process">The Process</h2>
      <div class="editorial-columns">
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Consultation.</strong> Goals, medical history, candidacy, and planning.</li>
          <li><strong>Treatment.</strong> Technique tailored to indication and area.</li>
          <li><strong>Review & Next Steps.</strong> What to expect and when maintenance might help.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-10 border-neutral-200">

      <!-- 5) Pre and Post‑Treatment Instructions -->
      <h2 id="pre-post">Pre and Post‑Treatment Instructions</h2>
      <div class="editorial-columns">
        <p>
          You’ll receive a brief handout tailored to your service. In general, arrive with clean skin, avoid irritants when advised,
          and follow simple do’s and don’ts after your session.
        </p>
        <h3>Before your visit</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Avoid new actives/irritants if directed</li>
          <li>Disclose medications, allergies, procedures</li>
          <li>Hydrate and arrive with clean skin</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>After your visit</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Follow your specific post‑care steps</li>
          <li>Protect from heat/sun and skip harsh actives</li>
          <li>Reach out with unexpected reactions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-10 border-neutral-200">

      <!-- 6) Frequently Asked Questions -->
      <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="editorial-columns">
        <p><strong>How many sessions will I need?</strong> It depends on your goals and indication. We outline a plan during your consult.</p>
        <p><strong>Will it look natural?</strong> We favor subtle, harmonious outcomes that respect your features and proportions.</p>
        <p><strong>Is there downtime?</strong> Most services have minimal downtime; we provide specifics and simple aftercare to follow.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">*Informational content only; not medical advice. Individual results vary.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
